7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:31:29+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015\n\nIn the contemporary world, every organization and company are compelled to make competitively much better"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"In the contemporary world, every organization and company are compelled to make competitively much better decisions, enhance client and customer service, provide quality services and products and increase potency to stay relevant and stand exemplary compared to the competition. There are a variety of explanations why almost every organizations and companies are keen to get ISO 9001 certification. QMS (quality management system) helps an organization to stay focused and serve the interests of various stakeholders. Over time, however, it has become necessary for every organization to switch from ISO 9001:2008 to ISO 9001:2015. Here's why and what are the reasons to switch from ISO 9001:2008 to ISO 9001:2015."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Differences in Structure"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Although both the editions are similar but when considering the first 3 clauses, the 2015 version includes a High Level Structure. This newer version encompasses a total of 10 clauses, a factor which makes it easier to integrate multiple management systems."}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Areas of Focus"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"In comparison to the 2008 version, 2015 one focuses more on every input and output of processes. This implies that quality emphasizes activity and closely assessing what goes into all methods and processes. Which is then often weighed against what a similar method produces."}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Risk-based Thinking"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"ISO 9001:2008 certification has risk-based thinking collectively of its centrepieces. With the ISO 9001:2008 certification, organizations have to be compelled to use outdated standard techniques to hold out a risk analysis to spot the challenges they face in managing almost every process. this suggests that the preventative measures captured in 9001:2008 are rendered redundant and not feature in the 2015 version."}],["$","p","8",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Context of the organization ISO 9001:2015"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"With ISO 9001:2015 certification, an organization or a company should be aware of the context with which it operates. What this insinuates is that you simply ought to take into consideration regarding the requirements of all interested parties and come up with the ways to react to those expectations effectively."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18"]}],"$L19"]}]}]
