e:[["$","title","0",{"children":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015 | ISO 9001:2008 Vs ISO 9001:2015 | What is new in ISO 9001:2015 | Wizms"}],["$","meta","1",{"name":"description","content":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015\n\nIn the contemporary world, every organization and company are compelled to make competitively much better"}],["$","meta","2",{"name":"keywords","content":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015"}],["$","meta","3",{"property":"og:title","content":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015 | ISO 9001:2008 Vs ISO 9001:2015 | What is new in ISO 9001:2015 | Wizms"}],["$","meta","4",{"property":"og:description","content":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015\n\nIn the contemporary world, every organization and company are compelled to make competitively much better"}],["$","meta","5",{"property":"og:url","content":"https://wizms.net/what-is-new-in-iso-9001-2015"}],["$","meta","6",{"property":"og:type","content":"article"}],["$","meta","7",{"property":"article:published_time","content":"2026-01-02T06:31:29+00:00"}],["$","meta","8",{"name":"twitter:card","content":"summary"}],["$","meta","9",{"name":"twitter:title","content":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015 | ISO 9001:2008 Vs ISO 9001:2015 | What is new in ISO 9001:2015 | Wizms"}],["$","meta","10",{"name":"twitter:description","content":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015\n\nIn the contemporary world, every organization and company are compelled to make competitively much better"}],["$","link","11",{"rel":"icon","href":"/favicon.ico"}],["$","$L1a","12",{}]]
10:["$","p","10",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Engagement of Interested Parties"}]
11:["$","p","11",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"While ISO 9001:2008 certification considered customers to be the sole interested party, whereas ISO 9001:2015 certification has enlarged this bracket which also includes suppliers, internal customers, personnel, legislative bodies, shareholders and therefore the larger society. Organizations got to bear this in mind and appreciate all these interested parties. The newer version of ISO certification additionally emphasizes leadership and commitment, requiring those in leadership positions to be much more concerned about the management and its QMS."}]
12:["$","p","12",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Benefits of the new edition (ISO 9001:2015)"}]
13:["$","p","13",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"ISO 9001:2015 certification includes a range of advantages over ISO 9001:2008. ISO 9001:2015 certification uses a lot of simplified languages and enhances effective supply chain management. This ISO certification is user-friendly and more acceptance will be practised especially for knowledge-based organizations. These benefits of ISO 9001:2015 afford additional focus and potency."}]
14:["$","p","14",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"ISO certification companies or consultancies work with you to manage and enhance the quality management of your systems. Their approach is additionally designed to determine whether or not you meet the quality requirements and also the level of compliance and effectiveness of your system. They will offer the required help and the supplier audits to confirm that the requirements of your organizations are met systematically"}]
15:["$","p","15",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"When the organization is desirous to improve their work in order to comply with ISO 9001 certification, workers, most of the time, apprehend before management what difficulties are encountered in the job. Often, workers are annoyed as a result of issues that don't seem to be detected or seem to be procrastinated. However, once evidence-based decisions are deployed, the workers will apprehend that their issues are valued and secured with the information required to work towards improvement. Decisions based on information mean that the knowledge of employees are often captured to learn and benefit both the workers the organization company."}]
16:["$","p","16",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Benefits for the employee are the benefits for the organization"}]
17:["$","p","17",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"While you may not implement ISO 9001 QMS standard simply to achieve benefits to the workers, these additional advantages can assist in improved worker retention and satisfaction, that is better for your company. Satisfied workers can stay longer in the company which is a gain that benefits their development from the ISO 9001 certification training which you have provided. You may save money on training new workers once dissatisfied employees leave."}]
18:["$","p","18",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Knowing that your workers will also have the benefit of your ISO 9001 implementation can even be some extent to make it easier to have interaction with employees in your business and draw from their information to make ISO 9001 Quality Management System work for you. Once implementing ISO 9001 is seen as a win-win situation for both the organization and the workers, the method and process of implementing is way easier and quicker to do. Therefore, work together with your workers so that everybody benefits."}]
19:["$","footer",null,{"className":"mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap gap-2","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"text-xs font-semibold text-gray-600 bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded","children":"Comparison of ISO 9001:2008 and ISO 9001:2015"}]]}]}]
